This is the older and first [[Wikipedia:PDP-10]] model, a KA10 in a large configuration: disk drives and printer in the foreground, CPU and DECtapes right center, memory cabinets to its left and a swapping disk and controller to their left, then data channels and 9-track tapes to its right. Sitting on the floor near the KA10 control panel: the [[Wikipedia:Teletype console]]. Just above the control panel and below the bottom DECtape drive is a paper-tape reader and/or punch (I think). Photo: from a DECsystem-10 sales brochure, courtesy of Michael Thompson, Retro-Computing Society of RI.
(cited from http://www.columbia.edu/acis/history/pdp10.html)

